rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.STUDYID

fields.definition: A unique identifier for a study.
fields.implementationNotes: While this field is not typically captured on a CRF, it should be displayed clearly on the CRF and/or the EDC system. This field can be included into the database or populated during SDTM-based dataset creation before submission.
fields.label: Study Identifier
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: STUDYID

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.SITEID

fields.definition: A unique identifier for a site within a study.
fields.implementationNotes: Paper: This is typically preprinted in the header of each CRF page for single site studies. For studies with multiple sites, this field may be left blank so that the number can be recorded by the site, or it may be preprinted for the CRFs that are shipped to each site. EDC: This should be prepopulated.
fields.label: Study Site Identifier
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: SITEID

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.SUBJID

fields.completionInstructions: Record the identifier for the subject.
fields.definition: A unique subject identifier within a site and a study.
fields.implementationNotes: Paper: This is typically recorded in the header of each CRF page. EDC: The subject identifiers may be provided to the site using a pre-populated list in the system. This CDASH variable is typically collected in all CDASH domains. However, this CDASH variable is populated only in the SDTMIG DM domain. For more information, refer to Study Data Tabulation Model.
fields.label: Subject Identifier for the Study
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: SUBJID

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.VISIT

fields.definition: The name of a clinical encounter that encompasses planned and unplanned trial interventions, procedures, and assessments that may be performed on a subject.
fields.implementationNotes: This CDASH variable is typically collected in all CDASH domains. However, this CDASH variable is represented only in the SDTMIG DM domain. For more information, refer to Study Data Tabulation Model, Table 2.2.4.
fields.label: Visit Name
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: VISIT

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.VISDAT

fields.completionInstructions: Record the [date/start date] of the visit using DD-MON-YYYY format.
fields.definition: Date the clinical encounter occurred (or started).
fields.implementationNotes: The date the inclusion and exclusion assessments were collected can be determined from the Visit Date variable (VISDAT) and applying that date to all of the observations at that visit or the collection date can be included on the Inclusion/Exclusion CRF using the date (IEDAT) field.
fields.label: Visit Date
fields.mappingInstructions: This field is not an SDTM variable. The date of a measurement, test, observation can be determined from the date/time of visit (VISDAT/VISTIM) and then concatenating the CDASH VISDAT/VISTIM components and populating the SDTMIG variable IEDTC in ISO 8601 format.
fields.name: VISDAT
fields.questionText: What [is/was] the date of the visit?

codelist.title: Version-agnostic anchor resource for codelist C66742

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IEYN

fields.completionInstructions: Record Yes if all eligibility criteria were met at the time the subject was enrolled. Record No if subject did not meet all criteria at the time the subject was enrolled.
fields.definition: Indication whether the subject met all the eligibility requirements for this study at the time the subject was enrolled.
fields.implementationNotes: The intent/purpose of collecting this field is to help with data cleaning and monitoring. It provides verification if all other fields on the CRF were deliberately left blank.
fields.label: Any Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Findings
fields.mappingInstructions: Does not map to an SDTMIG variable. The SDTM Annotated CRF is annotated to indicate that this field is NOT SUBMITTED.
fields.name: IEYN

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IEDAT

fields.completionInstructions: Record complete date when the eligibility assessment was performed using this format (DD-MON-YYYY).
fields.definition: The date of collection of the inclusion/exclusion criteria represented in an unambiguous date format. (e.g., DD-MON-YYYY).
fields.implementationNotes: A complete date is expected. The date of collection may be determined from the date of visit (VISDAT) and if so, a separate assessment date field is not required.
fields.label: Date of Inclusion/Exclusion Collection
fields.mappingInstructions: This does not map directly to an SDTMIG variable. For the SDTM submission dataset, concatenate all collected CDASH DATE and TIME components and populate the SDTMIG variable IEDTC in ISO 8601 format.
fields.name: IEDAT
fields.questionText: What was the date the eligibility criteria assessment was performed?

codelist.title: Version-agnostic anchor resource for codelist C66797

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IECAT

fields.completionInstructions: Record whether the criterion exception was Inclusion or Exclusion. Checkbox: Check Inclusion or Exclusion.
fields.definition: A grouping category to denote whether the protocol entry criterion being assessed is Inclusion Criteria or Exclusion Criteria
fields.implementationNotes: These categories have been pre-defined in SDTM and have controlled terminology that must be used. Only records for criteria that are not met appear in the IE SDTMIG domain. IECAT must be populated. This criterion category may be collected on the CRF in a checkbox format or it may be included as part of the Criterion Identification and mapped when the SDTM Submission datasets are created.
fields.label: Category of Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: IECAT
fields.questionText: What was the category of the criterion?

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IESCAT

fields.completionInstructions: If collected on the CRF, the sponsor provides instructions to ensure the data is entered as intended.
fields.definition: A sub-division of the IECAT values based on user defined characteristics.
fields.implementationNotes: Sponsor-defined Controlled Terminology. This would most commonly be either a heading, or a pre-printed category value on the CRF and not a question to which the site would provide an answer. If a question is asked, the response would typically be a sponsor-defined codelist. If the form is laid out as a grid, then words such as "Subcategory" can be included as the column header This can be used to distinguish criteria for a sub study or to categorize the criteria as a major or minor exception.
fields.label: Subcategory of Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: IESCAT
fields.questionText: What was the subcategory of the criterion?

implements.title: Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IETESTCD

fields.completionInstructions: If the subject was not eligible, Record the identifying code for each criterion that was an exception.
fields.definition: The unique identifier associated with the criterion that was the exception.
fields.implementationNotes: This field is required to appear on the CRF, but may be null if there are no exceptions to the inclusion/exclusion criteria. The CRF should allow multiple exceptions to be recorded. See SDTMIG V3.2 Section 7.5.2 for assumptions regarding protocol versioning. Sponsor may provide a list of inclusion/ exclusion criteria and the unique identifying codes to the site. The list provided should be versioned/updated when the protocol changes and the criteria are changed. Sponsor should use sponsor developed controlled terminology for IETESTCD.
fields.label: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: IETESTCD
fields.questionText: What was the identifier of the inclusion criterion the subject did not meet or the exclusion criterion the subject met ?

implements.title: Name of Measurement, Test or Examination

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IETEST

fields.completionInstructions: Record the description of the criterion, if not pre-printed on the CRF. If collected on the CRF, the sponsor may provide additional instructions to ensure the data is entered as intended.
fields.definition: Descriptive name of the inclusion or exclusion criterion that was the exception.
fields.implementationNotes: Sponsor's could automatically populated the text in EDC systems when the Criterion Identifier is populated by the investigator. This can be verified by the PI to ensure the right Exception Identifier was selected.
fields.label: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target". The SDTMIG variable IETESTCD may be determined from the value collected in IETEST. The SDTMIG variables IETESTCD and IETEST are required in the SDTM submission datasets.
fields.name: IETEST
fields.questionText: What was the description of the inclusion criterion the subject did not meet or the exclusion criterion the subject met?

implements.title: Result of Finding in Original Unit

parentProduct.title: Clinical Data Acquisition Standards Harmonization Implementation Guide for Human Clinical Trials Version 2.0

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor element for field IE.IEORRES

fields.completionInstructions: If collected on the CRF, the sponsor provides instructions to ensure the data is entered as intended.
fields.definition: An indication of which Inclusion criterion was not met or Exclusion criterion was met.
fields.implementationNotes: This is not a data collection field. When an Inclusion Criteria is not met, IEORRES will be mapped to "N" and when Exclusion Criteria is met, IEORRES is mapped to "Y". Only exceptions for a subject are included in the domain. This may be populated when the SDTM submission datasets are created, or in the operational data management system.
fields.label: I/E Criterion Result
fields.mappingInstructions: Maps directly to the SDTMIG variable listed in the column with the heading "SDTMIG Target".
fields.name: IEORRES
